        <section>
            <h2>Sustainability</h2>
            <p>Sustainability is something that focuses on meeting the needs of the present without
                compromising the
                needs
                of
                the future, a way of maintaining itself functioning without ever ceasing to be.</p>
            <p>Sustainability is a concept that goes way beyond simple "recycling", it is a complex matter
                that
                diverges
                into
                various topics which can be placed into three main pillars.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>The Social Pillar:</h2>
            <p>The most vague of the three, it can be hard to understand how or why "social
                sustainability"
                exists
                but,
                implementing changes is a social challenge in of itself, it can easily affect our
                individual
                lifestyle,
                ethical
                consumerism, means of transportation, etc.</p>
            <p>Not to mention it can also embed topics such as social equity, livability, community
                development,
                human
                rights and personal responsibility. </p>

