        <section>
            <h2>The Economic Pillar:</h2>
            <p>"To be sustainable, a business must be profitable", a sentence most businesses are
                well akin to,
                and
                though
                it does play a big role into our society one must not weight it heavier than the
                other two.</p>
            <p>Still, our and the companies financial well-being must take part in the equation for
                embracing
                such
                sustainability strategies can come at some expenses.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>The Environmental Pillar:</h2>
            <div>
                <p>Perhaps the most well known of the three, as the name suggests this pillar is entirely
                    focused on
                    the
                    environment and saving it from the many things that aim to endanger it.</p>
                <p>Trying to reduce our carbon footprints, waste, water usage can have an astonishing impact
                    to our
                    duty
                    of
                    saving
                    the planet.</p>
                <p>But there is much more than can be done, not just by us simple civilians but also major
                    companies,
                    from
                    lessening the ammount of harmful material into packaging products
                    or simply replace them with other healthier alternatives.</p>
